The paper deals with the forensic analysis of mobile VoIP apps on Android devices, which involves investigating the remnants of these apps to extract forensically valuable information. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with the privacy and security concerns related to the use of these apps. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the data stored on the smartphone device, which could fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cloud computing (cs.DC), cybercrime and cybersecurity (cs.CY), software engineering (cs.SE), and databases (cs.DB).
